overview: The user initiated an urgent request to fix a pull request with
  multiple issues, including critical security flaws and broken Vercel
  deployments. The assistant systematically identified and addressed a
  comprehensive list of problems from a bot review and CI failures. Key fixes
  included replacing an insecure admin authentication cookie with HMAC-signed
  sessions, implementing pagination and validation for API data endpoints,
  correcting PDF generation logic for accurate sleep metrics and dynamic user
  names, and enabling null values for number inputs. A significant challenge was
  ensuring the authentication logic worked within Vercel's Edge Runtime, which
  was resolved by refactoring the crypto operations to use the Web Crypto API.
  All changes were committed and pushed, leading to a successful local build and
  a new CI run.
